Date: Sat 12 Feb 2000
From: Steve Toovey <toovey@travelclinic.co.za>
Subject: Rabies - UK: pet quarantine changed (02)

Porthmadog is not a veterinary service, despite the appearance of the name.
Welsh colleagues will hopefully forgive the simplistic English
pronunciation of the name as something usually resembling "Port Madock."
This is situated in the county of Gwynedd, pronounced "Gwynneth." This is a
county in North Wales where Welsh is spoken extensively.
--
Dr Steve Toovey
British Airways Travel Clinic
Johannesburg
<toovey@travelclinic.co.za>
